<!DOCTYPE html>
<html class="h-100" lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include('partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body class="d-flex flex-column h-100">
    <header><%- include('partials/header') %></header>
    <main class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row justify-content-between">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-7">
          <h1 class="mt-2 mb-4 ml-5">Welcome to Harmony Dog</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-md-5 text-center">
          <!-- Demo account idea comes from Matthew Mitchell @https://www.linkedin.com/in/codebymatthew/ a fellow #100Dev developer and all around solid human being -->
          <!-- Hidden form allows users to check out application with pre-defined account instead of having to make an account-->
          <!-- user.privileges was set in MongoDB as demo, which will conditionally disable certain buttons in app to help prevent abuse-->
          <form action="/login" method="POST">
            <input
              type="hidden"
              id="userEmail"
              name="userEmail"
              value="bojangles@gmail.com"
            />
            <input
              type="hidden"
              name="password"
              id="password"
              value="hewilldanceforyou"
            />
            <button class="btn btn-outline-success my-3 mr-5" type="submit">
              Look around with a demo account
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>
        <!-- end demo account form code-->
      </div>
      <div class="row justify-content-center justify-content-lg-center">
        <div class="col-10 col-lg-7 ml-5">
          <!-- Begin carousel -->
          <div
            id="carouselExampleIndicators"
            class="carousel slide m-auto"
            data-ride="carousel"
          >
            <ol class="carousel-indicators">
              <li
                data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators"
                data-slide-to="0"
                class="active"
              ></li>
              <li
                data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators"
                data-slide-to="1"
              ></li>
              <li
                data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators"
                data-slide-to="2"
              ></li>
              <li
                data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators"
                data-slide-to="3"
              ></li>
              <li
                data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators"
                data-slide-to="4"
              ></li>
            </ol>
            <div class="carousel-inner">
              <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img
                  class="d-block"
                  src="/images/anoir_chafik_puppies.JPG"
                  alt="First slide"
                />
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                  <h5>Puppies' First Steps</h5>
                  <p>Set your puppy off on the right foot</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="carousel-item">
                <img
                  class="d-block"
                  src="/images/bundo_kim_dogsMeeting.JPG"
                  alt="Second slide"
                />
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                  <h5>Good Dog Citizen</h5>
                  <p>Help your dog learn basic dog etiquette</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="carousel-item">
                <img
                  class="d-block"
                  src="/images/jamie_street_smartDog.JPG"
                  alt="Third slide"
                />
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                  <h5>Next Level Learning</h5>
                  <p>Understand the basics of shaping behavior</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="carousel-item">
                <img
                  class="d-block"
                  src="/images/madalyn_cox_olderDog.JPG"
                  alt="Fourth slide"
                />
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                  <h5>Older Dog Changes</h5>
                  <p>As fido ages you'll need to learn how to adapt</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="carousel-item">
                <img
                  class="d-block"
                  src="/images/wade_austin_ellis_dogAndOwner.JPG"
                  alt="Fifth slide"
                />
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                  <h5>Strong Bonds</h5>
                  <p>Learn how to communicate with your pup effectively</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
              class="carousel-control-prev"
              href="#carouselExampleIndicators"
              role="button"
              data-slide="prev"
            >
              <span
                class="carousel-control-prev-icon"
                aria-hidden="true"
              ></span>
              <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
            </a>
            <a
              class="carousel-control-next"
              href="#carouselExampleIndicators"
              role="button"
              data-slide="next"
            >
              <span
                class="carousel-control-next-icon"
                aria-hidden="true"
              ></span>
              <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
            </a>
          </div>
          <!-- End carousel -->
        </div>
        <!-- End column -->

        <div class="col-10 col-lg-4 py-4">
          <!-- These tips will eventually be generated dynamically from a database -->
          <!-- There will also be a general tips page, perhaps a blog like format-->
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <h3>Training tip of the week</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="card mb-3" style="width: 18rem">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Training Tip #36</h5>
                <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Sit & Stay</h6>
                <p class="card-text">
                  While sit is a simple request for many dogs, stay is more
                  complicated. Make sure your pet's sit is strong and persistent
                  and then work slowly while increasing distances of stay.
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="card-link">Learn More</a>
                <a href="#" class="card-link">More tips</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="card mb-3" style="width: 18rem">
              <img
                src="/images/justin_veenema_onLeash.JPG"
                class="card-img-top"
                alt="Photo by Justin Veenema on >Unsplash"
              />
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Training Tip #4</h5>
                <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">Behaving on leash</h6>
                <p class="card-text">
                  The physical connection of the leash between dog and owner can
                  prompt some less-desirable behaviors in our pets. Knowing what
                  to do, and what to avoid when on leash can be complicate.
                  Develop a leash plan before 'bad' behaviors become ingrained.
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="card-link">Learn More</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="card mb-3" style="width: 18rem">
              <img
                src="/images/aaron_james_kennel.JPG"
                class="card-img-top"
                alt="Photo by Aaron James on Unsplash"
              />
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Training Tip #78</h5>
                <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-muted">
                  Feeling safe in a kennel
                </h6>
                <p class="card-text">
                  Kennels are important to our pets. Travel and time alone are
                  both easier with a strong association of safety with kennels.
                  Avoid using kennels as a 'time-out spaces' because of the
                  long-term difficulties it can introduce into your pet
                  management plans.
                </p>
                <a href="#" class="card-link">Learn More</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- End Column-->
      </div>
      <!-- End Row-->
    </main>
    <footer class="footer light-blue mt-auto py-3">
      <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </footer>
    <%- include('partials/scripts') %>
  </body>
</html>
